{"questionId":"17009","questionHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">An object undergoes simple harmonic motion (shm) of amplitude <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math></em><sub>0</sub>. When the displacement of the object is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msub><mi>x</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math>, the speed of the object is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math></em>. What is the speed when the displacement is <em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math></em><sub>0</sub>?</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">A. 0</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">B.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi>v</mi><mn>3</mn></mfrac></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><msqrt><mn>2</mn></msqrt><mn>3</mn></mfrac><mi>v</mi></math></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">D.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn><mi>v</mi></math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"17009","referenceCode":"19N.1.HL.TZ0.26","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An object undergoes simple harmonic motion (shm) of amplitude x0. When the displacement of the object is x03, the speed of the object is v. What is the speed when the displacement ","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"26","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena","9.1 – Simple harmonic motion","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 9: Wave phenomena"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}